{
  "schema_version": "ebook-layout.v1",
  "book": {
    "title": "Habit Design Workbook",
    "description": "A practical workbook for building small habits that survive real schedules, low motivation, and busy weeks.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "volume": "Vol. 1",
    "footer": "Small Systems for Everyday Change"
  },
  "layout": {
    "template": "habit-workbook",
    "theme": "navy-yellow",
    "page_size": "a4"
  },
  "chapters": [
    {
      "id": "chapter-01",
      "order": 1,
      "slug": "make-it-obvious",
      "title": "Make It Obvious",
      "sections": {
        "hook": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "A habit is easier to start when the environment reminds you before willpower has to work."
            }
          ]
        },
        "concept": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Most missed habits are not failures of character."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "They are often failures of visibility."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "When the cue is hidden, the habit depends on memory."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Design the cue so it appears at the exact moment you want the action to happen."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Use placement, timing, and pairing with an existing routine."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The best cue is simple enough that you notice it even on a tired day."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Make the next action visible before you need motivation."
            }
          ]
        },
        "examples": [
          {
            "category": "Health",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Put a full water bottle next to your keyboard before you go to sleep."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "category": "Work",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Leave tomorrow's first task written on a sticky note at the center of your desk."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "drills": [
          {
            "number": 1,
            "title": "Cue Placement Map",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Choose one small habit you want to repeat this week."
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Examples:"
              },
              {
                "type": "unordered_list",
                "items": ["drink water after waking", "stretch after work", "review tomorrow's plan"]
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Now answer this:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Where should the cue live so I will see it at the right moment?"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Habit:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Current cue:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Better cue location:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Set the cue today, not later."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "reflection": {
          "prompts": [
            "Which cue was easiest to notice?",
            "Where did the habit still get hidden?",
            "What will I move, prepare, or label tonight?"
          ],
          "closing": "A visible cue turns intention into a simple invitation."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "chapter-02",
      "order": 2,
      "slug": "make-it-small",
      "title": "Make It Small",
      "sections": {
        "hook": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The habit that survives a messy day is the one that is small enough to begin."
            }
          ]
        },
        "concept": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Ambitious habits often fail because the starting line is too far away."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "A tiny version protects consistency."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The goal is not to make the habit impressive at first."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The goal is to make the beginning almost frictionless."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Once you start, you can always do more."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Shrink the action until it can fit inside your worst realistic day."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Consistency grows faster when the minimum version is clear."
            }
          ]
        },
        "examples": [
          {
            "category": "Learning",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Read one page before opening social media, then continue only if you want to."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "category": "Health",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Do two push-ups or one minute of mobility instead of promising a full workout."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "drills": [
          {
            "number": 1,
            "title": "Minimum Version",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Write the habit you actually want."
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Examples:"
              },
              {
                "type": "unordered_list",
                "items": ["exercise daily", "study a language", "clean the kitchen"]
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Now answer this:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "What is the smallest version I can do even when the day goes badly?"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Full habit:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Two-minute version:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "When I will do it:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Keep the minimum version almost laughably small."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "reflection": {
          "prompts": [
            "What habit did I make smaller?",
            "Did the smaller version feel easier to begin?",
            "What would make it even more frictionless?"
          ],
          "closing": "A small start keeps the chain alive."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "chapter-03",
      "order": 3,
      "slug": "make-it-reviewable",
      "title": "Make It Reviewable",
      "sections": {
        "hook": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "A habit system improves when you can see what happened without judging yourself."
            }
          ]
        },
        "concept": {
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Tracking is useful when it creates feedback, not guilt."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "A weekly review helps you notice patterns."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "You can see which cues worked, which days were overloaded, and which habit was too large."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Review the system before blaming yourself."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The question is not whether you were perfect."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The question is what the week taught you about the design."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Adjust the cue, size, or timing based on evidence."
            }
          ]
        },
        "examples": [
          {
            "category": "Work",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "If deep work failed every afternoon, move it before meetings instead of trying harder."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "category": "Money",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "If expense tracking failed at night, enter purchases immediately after paying."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "drills": [
          {
            "number": 1,
            "title": "Seven-Day Review",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Pick one habit you tried for at least a few days."
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Examples:"
              },
              {
                "type": "unordered_list",
                "items": ["morning walk", "daily budget check", "evening shutdown routine"]
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Now answer this:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "What does the last week show about my habit design?"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "What worked:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "What got in the way:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "What I will change next week:"
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Treat the review as calibration, not criticism."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "reflection": {
          "prompts": [
            "What pattern appeared more than once?",
            "Which habit design needs adjustment?",
            "What is my next one-week experiment?"
          ],
          "closing": "A review turns effort into learning."
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
